IN line with the youth empowerment policy of the Oyo State government, Fullrange Microfinance Bank as one of the financial institutions domiciled in the state has offered loan facility to transporters to boost their businesses. Christened Ride to Own, the loan is for public transport operators who want to own Tricycle and Nissan Micra car which is renowned among cab operators in the state. The loan which is in a form of asset financing, according to the Head, Account and Finance of the bank, Toyosi Adekanmbi, is payable within 15 months after which the ownership of the Tricycle or Nissan Micra car will be transferred to the beneficiary. Education: The Abiodun intervention in Ogun #SexForGrades scandal: Atiku says ‘It’s an… SDP constitutes caretaker committee for party in Osun Kogi election: Natasha Akpoti has neither compromised nor… ALSO READ: https://tribuneonlineng.com/el-rufais-wife-pledges-empowerment-loan-for-women/ Adekanmbi, noted that Fullrange Microfinance Bank is launching the product not primarily to make money, but as a way of contributing to the economic development of the state. Head, Credit Administration of the bank, Olatilewa Ishola, hinted that those who signified interest in the loan have started receiving their tricycles and cars at the bank’s corporate headquarters in Ibadan. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
